      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>Homily on <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3899Eudoxia">
                  ʾAwdoksyā
                 
               </t:persName>, wife of Emperor <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2016Arcadius">
                  ʾArqādewos
               </t:persName> and on 
               a certain Yoḥannǝs, who could be identified with <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10390Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs [I]</t:persName> 
               following <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/VCHI8RJJ"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM"/><title level="a">Dǝrsanä Mikaʾel</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Gianfrancesco</forename><surname>Lusini</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2005</date><biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">139a-140a</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM</note></t:bibl>, but according to <t:persName ref="#DN"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: DN</span></t:persName>, is more 
               likely to be identified with <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5720JohnChr">John Chrysostom</t:persName> due to the manuscripts' usual formulation 
               <t:q xml:lang="gez">baʾǝnta Yoḥannǝs</t:q>. It is usually transmitted in the section for the month Gǝnbot.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
